[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Theoretical research shows that an optimized bidirectional approach can be instance-optimal, meaning no correct algorithm can asymptotically relax fewer edges on the same graph instance.
[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Although Dijkstra's algorithm is optimal for graphs with non-negative edge weights, its practical runtime depends on both data structures and graph properties.
