[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Graph structure also plays a major role.
[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Sparse networks, such as road maps, allow Dijkstra's algorithm to operate efficiently since most vertices have low degree.
[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Dense graphs increase relaxations and slow down the process.
[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Because of this, modern routing systems often use Dijkstra's algorithm together with preprocessing methods such as A* search, landmark heuristics, or contraction hierarchies, which significantly reduce the search space.
[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Memory locality is another important factor.
