[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/weighted-graph-p01] A graph property is closed under some operation on graphs if, whenever the argument or arguments to the operation have the property, then so does the result.
[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/weighted-graph-p01] For instance, hereditary properties are closed under induced subgraphs; monotone properties are closed under subgraphs; and minor-closed properties are closed under minors.
[src:dijkstra-shortest-path/weighted-graph-p01] A closure of a directed graph is a set of vertices that have no outgoing edges to vertices outside the closure.
